# To move swiftly.
## {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[move]] forward [[quickly]] upon [[two]] [[feet]] by alternately making a short [[jump]] off either foot.
##: {{cot|en|walk}}
##: {{ux|en|'''Run''', and you might still catch the train!}}
##* {{quote-book|en|year=1967|author=w:Barbara Sleigh|title=w:Jessamy| year_published=1993| location=Sevenoaks, Kent| publisher=Bloomsbury |isbn=0 340 19547 9| page=122| passage=Through the open front door '''ran''' Jessamy, down the steps to where Kitto was sitting at the bottom with the pram beside him.}}
##* {{see more citations|en}}<!-- Please no more than 3â€“4 quotes here, further quotes only in 'Citations' (see [[WT:QUOTE]])-->
## {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[go]] at a [[fast]] pace; to move [[quickly]].
##: {{ux|en|I have been '''running''' all over the building looking for him.}}
##: {{ux|en|Sorry, I've got to '''run'''; my house is on fire!}}
##* {{quote-song|en|author=w:Ed Cobb|authorlabel=no|title=w:Tainted Love|album=w:Non-Stop Erotic Cabaret|year=1965|year_published=1981|artist=w:Soft Cell|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XZVpR3Pk-r8|text=Once I '''ran''' to you (I ran) / Now I '''run''' from you / This tainted love you've given / I give you all a boy could give you}}
## {{lb|en|transitive}} To cover (a course or a distance) by running.
##: {{ux|en|I can '''run''' a mile, but I can't '''run''' the cross-country course.}}
## {{lb|en|transitive}} To complete a running course or event in (a given time).
##: {{ux|en|I was hoping to make the team, but I didn't '''run''' the qualifying time.}}
## {{lb|en|intransitive}} To move briskly or smoothly with a motion of sliding, rolling, sweeping etc.
##: {{ux|en|The shuttle '''runs''' back and forth on these rollers.}}
##: {{ux|en|As its name suggests, the monorail '''runs''' on a single rail.}}
##: {{ux|en|I felt her fingers '''running''' over my cheek.}}
## {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[cause]] to move [[quickly]] or [[lightly]].
##: {{ux|en|Every day I '''run''' my dog across the field and back.}}
##: {{ux|en|I'll just '''run''' the vacuum cleaner over the carpet.}}
##: {{ux|en|'''Run''' your fingers through my hair.}}
##: {{ux|en|'''Run''' a flag up (the pole/mast)}}
##* {{RQ:Doyle Lost World|passage=Challenger and I '''ran''' Summerlee along, one at each of his elbows, while Lord John covered our retreat, firing again and again as savage heads snarled at us out of the bushes.}}
## {{senseid|en|race}} {{lb|en|transitive|or|intransitive}} To [[compete]] in a [[race]].
##: {{ux|en|The horse will '''run''' in the Preakness next year.}}
##: {{ux|en|I'm not ready to '''run''' a marathon.}}
##: {{ux|en|The car could not be repaired in time for the race and did not '''run'''. }}
## {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[transport]] (someone or something), notionally at a brisk pace.
##: {{ux|en|Could you '''run''' me over to the store?}}
##: {{ux|en|Please '''run''' this report upstairs to director's office.}}
## {{lb|en|transitive|intransitive}} Of a means of transportation: to [[travel]] (a [[route]]).
##: {{ux|en|The bus (train, plane, ferry boat, etc) '''runs''' between Newport and Riverside.}}
