## {{lb|en|transitive}} To cause (a  vehicle) to  travel a route.
##* {{quote-journal|en|year=2024|month=11|journal=Lackawanna Coalition Railgram|author=David Peter Alan|title=NJ Transit Runs Special Trains to â€œRailroad Museum [for a day]â€|url=https://lackawannacoalition.org/2024/11/25/nj-transit-runs-special-trains-to-railroad-museum-for-a-day/|text=This year, NJ Transit allowed nonmotorists {{â€¦}} to reach the event by '''running''' special trains every 2 hours 4 round trips). The location was the old Lackawanna Railroad freight house, about a 10-minute walk from the Boonton Station, which normally has service only during peak-commuting hours on weekdays.}}
