===Noun===
[[File:Stairway Measurements.svg|thumb|diagram of stairs, showing the ''run'' ({{senseno|en|stair}})]]
[[File:Stocking run.jpg|thumb|upright=0.5|Stockings with a '''run''' ({{senseno|en|knit}}) in them]]
{{en-noun}}

# Act or instance of running, of moving rapidly using the feet.
#: {{ux|en|I just got back from my morning '''run'''.}}
#* {{quote-web|en|date=June 9, 2012|author=Owen Phillips| title=Euro 2012: Netherlands 0-1 Denmark| work=BBC Sport| url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/18138777| passage=Krohn-Dehli took advantage of a lucky bounce of the ball after a battling '''run''' on the left flank by Simon Poulsen, dummied two defenders and shot low through goalkeeper Maarten Stekelenburg's legs after 24 minutes.}}
# Act or instance of [[hurry]]ing (to or from a place) {{qualifier|not necessarily on foot}}; [[dash]] or [[errand]], [[trip]].
#: {{ux|en|I need to make a '''run''' to the store.}}
#* '''1759''', N. Tindal, ''The Continuation of Mr Rapin's History of England'', volume 21 (continuation volume 9), page 92:
#*: {{...}} and on the 18th of January this squadron put to sea. The first place of rendezvous was the boy of port St. Julian, upon the coast of Patagonia, and all accidents were provided against with admirable foresight. Their '''run''' to port St. Julian was dangerous {{...}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=25 Apr 87|journal=Gay Community News|page=1|author=Kim Westheimer|title=A Black Gay Fireman's Story|text=Jackson said the white firefighters attempted to make him and other Black firefighters miss '''runs''' by not waking them up along with everyone else.}}
# A pleasure trip.
#: {{ux|en|Let's go for a '''run''' in the car.}}
#* {{RQ:Dickens Martin Chuzzlewit|30
|passage=And I think of giving her a '''run''' in London for a change.}}
# [[flight|Flight]], instance or [[period]] of [[flee]]ing.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2006|author=Tsirk Susej|title=The Demonic Bible|isbn=1411690737|page=41|passage=During his '''run''' from the police, he claimed to have a metaphysical experience which can only be described as â€œhaving passed through an abyss.â€}}
# [[migration|Migration]] of [[fish]].
# A group of fish that migrate, or ascend a river for the purpose of spawning.
# A literal or figurative path or course for movement relating to:
## A (regular) [[trip]] or [[route]].
##: {{ux|en|The bus on the Cherry Street '''run''' is always crowded.}}
##* '''1977''', ''Star Wars'' (film)
##*: You've never heard of the Millennium Falcon? It's the ship that made the Kessel '''Run''' in less than twelve parsecs.
## The [[route]] taken while running or skiing.
##: {{ux|en|Which '''run''' did you do today?}}
## {{lb|en|skiing|bobsledding}} A single trip down a hill, as in [[skiing]] and [[bobsledding]].
## The distance sailed by a ship.
##: {{ux|en|a good '''run'''; a '''run''' of fifty miles}}
## A [[voyage]].
##: {{ux|en|a '''run''' to China}}
## A [[trial]].
##: {{ux|en|The data got lost, so I'll have to perform another '''run''' of the experiment.}}
## {{lb|en|maths|computing}} The [[execution]] of a [[program]] or [[model]]
##: {{ux|en|This morning's '''run''' of the SHIPS statistical model gave Hurricane Priscilla a 74% chance of gaining at least 30 knots of intensity in 24 hours, reconfirmed by the HMON and GFS dynamical models.}}
## {{lb|en|video games|speedrunning}} A [[playthrough]], or attempted playthrough; a session of play.
##: {{ux|en|This was my first successful '''run''' without losing any health.}}
##: {{ux|en|That NPC bugged out and killed my '''run'''.}}
# Unrestricted use. {{only used in|en|have the run of}}. <!--and "given" the run of, etc.-->
#: {{ux|en|He can have the '''run''' of the house.}}
# An [[enclosure]] for an animal; a [[track]] or [[path]] along which something can travel.
#: {{ux|en|He set up a rabbit '''run'''.}}
# {{senseid|en|landholding}}{{lb|en|Australia|New Zealand}} A [[rural#Adjective|rural]] [[landholding]] for [[farm#Verb|farming]], usually for [[run#Verb|running]] [[sheep]], and [[operate]]d by a [[runholder]].
# State of being current; currency; popularity.
#* {{RQ:Addison Freeholder|45|May 25, 1715|passage=It is impossible for detached papers[...] to have a general '''run''', or long continuance, if they are not diversified[...].}}
# Something continuous or sequential.
## A continuous period (of time) marked by a trend; a period marked by a continuing trend.
##: {{ux|en|Iâ€™m having a '''run''' of bad luck.}}
##* '''1782''' {{smallcaps|{{w|Frances Burney}}}} ''{{w|Cecilia (Burney novel)|Cecilia}}''
##*: â€œ{{...}}had had the preceding night an uncommon '''''run''' of luck''â€.
##: {{ux|en|He went to Las Vegas and spent all his money over a three-day '''run'''.}}
##* {{RQ:Burke Regicide Peace
|passage=They who made their arrangements in the first '''run''' of misadventure [...] put a seal on their calamities.}}
##* {{quote-journal|en|date=June 28, 2011| author=Piers Newbery| title=Wimbledon 2011: Sabine Lisicki beats Marion Bartoli| work=BBC Sport| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/tennis/13946420.stm| passage=German wildcard Sabine Lisicki conquered her nerves to defeat France's Marion Bartoli and take her amazing Wimbledon '''run''' into the semi-finals.}}
## A series of tries in a game that were successful.
##: {{ux|en|If our team can keep up their strong defense, expect them to make a '''run''' in this tournament.}}
## A production quantity (such as in a factory).
##: {{ux|en|Yesterday we did a '''run''' of 12,000 units.}}
##: {{ux|en|The bookâ€™s initial press '''run''' will be 5,000 copies.}}
## The period of showing of a play, film, TV series, etc.
##: {{ux|en|The '''run''' of the show lasted two weeks, and we sold out every night.}}
##: {{ux|en|It is the last week of our French cinema '''run'''.}}
##* {{RQ:Macaulay Goldsmith|passage=A canting, mawkish play [...] had an immense '''run'''.}}
## {{lb|en|slang}} A period of extended (usually [[daily]]) drug use.
##* {{quote-text|en|year=1964|title=Heroin|author=w:The Velvet Underground
|passage=And I'll tell ya, things aren't quite the same / When I'm rushing on my '''run'''.}}
##* {{quote-text|en|year=1975|author=Lloyd Y. Young; Mary Anne Koda-Kimble; Brian S. Katcher|title=Applied Therapeutics for Clinical Pharmacists
|passage=Frank Fixwell, a 25 year-old male, has been on a heroin "'''run'''" (daily use) for the past two years.}}
##* '''1977''', Richard P. Rettig, Manual J. Torres, Gerald R. Garrett, ''Manny: a criminal-addict's story'', Houghton Mifflin Harcourt (HMH) {{ISBN|9780395248386}}
##*: I was hooked on dope, and hooked bad, during this whole period, but I was also hooked behind robbery. When you&#39;re on a heroin '''run''', you stay loaded so long as you can score.
##* {{quote-book|en|year=2001|author=Robin J. Harman|title=Handbook of Pharmacy Health Education|publisher=Pharmaceutical Press|isbn=9780853694717|page=172
|passage=This can develop quite quickly (over a matter of hours) during a cocaine '''run''' or when cocaine use becomes a daily habit.}}
