|passage=DA depletion leads to the crash that characteristically ends a cocaine '''run'''.}}
## {{lb|en|card games}} A sequence of [[cards]] in a [[suit]] in a card game.
## {{lb|en|music}} A [[rapid]] [[passage]] in [[music]], especially along a [[scale]].
# {{senseid|en|liquid}}A flow of [[liquid]]; a [[leak]].
#: {{ux|en|The constant '''run''' of water from the faucet annoys me.}}
#: {{ux|en|a '''run''' of must in wine-making}}
#: {{ux|en|the first '''run''' of sap in a maple orchard}}
# {{lb|en|chiefly|eastern|_|North Midland US|especially|Ohio|Pennsylvania|West Virginia}} A small [[creek]] or part thereof. {{qualifier|Compare Southern US ''[[branch]]'' and New York and New England ''[[brook]]''.}}
#: {{ux|en|The military campaign near that creek was known as "The battle of Bull '''Run'''".}}
# A [[quick]] [[pace]], faster than a [[walk]].
#: {{ux|en|He broke into a '''run'''.}}
## {{lb|en|of horses}} A fast [[gallop]].
# {{lb|en|banking}} A sudden series of demands on a [[bank]] or other financial institution, especially characterised by great withdrawals.
#: {{ux|en|Financial insecurity led to a '''run''' on the banks, as customers feared for the security of their savings.}}
# Any sudden large [[demand]] for something.
#: {{ux|en|There was a '''run''' on Christmas presents.}}
# Various horizontal dimensions or surfaces
## The top of a [[step]] on a [[staircase]], also called a [[tread]], as opposed to the [[rise]].
## {{senseid|en|stair}} The horizontal length of a set of stairs
## {{lb|en|construction}} [[horizontal|Horizontal]] [[dimension]] of a [[slope]].
# A standard or unexceptional group or category.
#: {{ux|en|He stood out from the usual '''run''' of applicants.}}
# {{n-g|In sports}}
## {{lb|en|baseball}} A [[score]] when a [[runner]] touches all [[base]]s legally; the act of a runner scoring.
## {{lb|en|cricket}} The act of passing from one [[wicket]] to another; the [[point]] scored for this.
## {{lb|en|American football}} A running play.
